<DOC><DOCNO> AP890130-0125 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-30-89 1726EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-WhiteHouse-Tower     01-30 0149</FIRST><SECOND>AM-White House-Tower,130</SECOND><HEAD>Tower's Comments on Kremlin Don't Reflect Firm U.S. View</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   White House press secretary Marlin Fitzwatersaid Monday that a warning about the Soviet Union bydefense-secretary designate John Tower did not reflect theconclusions of a U.S. review of policies toward the Kremlin.   Fitzwater said Tower ``was, of course, speaking for theadministration in the sense that he was our nominee for thesecretary of defense. ... They (the remarks) don't reflect theconclusions of a government-wide review but they certainly reflecthis views, and as secretary of defense he'll have a very strong rolein the positions that are taken and in the reviews that take place.''   Tower, at a NATO conference in Munich, said Sunday that Moscowremains a powerful adversary. He urged NATO officials to remainskeptical of Moscow's disarmament overtures and to keep the West'snuclear options open.</TEXT></DOC>